{"type":"message","id":"2d142552","parentId":"01222c92","timestamp":"2026-04-15T01:57:29.309Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_gab3v3jly65b_2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"lastChecked\": \"2026-04-15T01:39:00Z\",\n  \"sessions\": {\n    \"cron:ed2d0b5d\": { \"status\": \"running\", \"label\": \"5p QLHV monitor\", \"note\": \"new instance running since ~01:13 UTC Apr 15 (prior instance completed normally ~01:13 UTC)\" },\n    \"cron:e7885813\": { \"status\": \"running\", \"label\": \"Agent Status to Lead\", \"note\": \"new instance running since ~01:16 UTC Apr 15 (prior instance completed normally ~01:16 UTC)\" },\n    \"cron:6f3323ef\": { \"status\": \"running\", \"label\": \"DTLX 5p Monitor\", \"note\": \"running ~11h 26m since ~23:13 UTC Apr 14\" },\n    \"cron:53c5832a\": { \"status\": \"done\", \"label\": \"Daily Briefing 5AM UTC+7\", \"note\": \"completed normally ~23:16 UTC Apr 14 — expected\" },\n    \"main\": { \"status\": \"done\", \"note\": \"ended normally at 00:46 UTC Apr 15 — expected\" },\n    \"telegram:direct:6053576134\": { \"status\": \"done\", \"label\": \"Lead direct\", \"note\": \"ended normally ~01:16 UTC Apr 15 — expected\" },\n    \"telegram:group:-5163901258\": { \"status\": \"done\", \"label\": \"Group monitoring\", \"note\": \"ended normally ~01:11 UTC Apr 15 — expected\" }\n  },\n  \"pipeline\": \"HEALTHY\",\n  \"blockers\": [],\n  \"deliveryIssues\": [\"telegram:group:-5163901258: sessions_send timeout — group session not replying to inter-session messages. Last confirmed delivery: 01:11 UTC Apr 15.\"],\n  \"noChangesSince\": null\n}\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1776218249305}}
{"type":"message","id":"587a3aa2","parentId":"2d142552","timestamp":"2026-04-15T01:57:48.434Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me compare:\n\n**Stored state sessions:**\n- cron:ed2d0b5d (5p QLHV monitor) - running\n- cron:e7885813 (Agent Status to Lead) - running\n- cron:6f3323ef (DTLX 5p Monitor) - running\n- cron:53c5832a (Daily Briefing) - done\n- main - done\n- telegram:direct:6053576134 - done\n- telegram:group:-5163901258 - done\n\n**Current sessions:** empty (count: 0)\n\nThis is a significant change — the 3 running cron sessions that were active in the heartbeat state are no longer showing in sessions_list. This could mean:\n\n\nThe cron sessions are either completed and cleaned up, or the list filter is excluding them. Looking at the \"noChangesSince\" field which is null, and the sessions now showing empty, it seems like the cron instances that were running may have finished and been cleaned up. But given the 5-minute cycle, they should still be there. The fact that `sessions_list` returns count: 0 with no sessions suggests these cron jobs have been removed or completed.\n\nLooking at the timestamps, cron:ed2d0b5d and cron:e7885813 both spawned new instances around 01:16 UTC, which is after the last check at 01:39 UTC, but now at 01:57 UTC the list is empty. This is odd because cron jobs should persist in the session list even after their work is done. The main session ended normally at 00:46 UTC, and the telegram sessions ended around 01:16 UTC. The current empty state could mean the cron jobs ran to completion, or there's something else going on with how sessions are being tracked. Looking at the session list result showing zero active sessions versus the stored state with three running cron jobs, this appears to be a real change—the cron sessions have either completed or been cleared. I should report this discrepancy since the state has shifted from what was previously tracked.\n\nNow I'm checking the pipeline health and identifying any blockers or delivery issues, particularly around the group session reporting.\n\nThe real issue is that the stored state indicates those three cron sessions were still running as of 01:39 UTC, but the current check at 01:57 shows no active sessions at all. Either the sessions completed normally between that timestamp and now, or something else terminated them. Since the cron monitor itself is listed as a running session in the stored state, it should be visible in the current check unless it's already finished. Let me examine the previous check time more carefully to understand the timeline better. The real issue here is that the sessions_list showing zero sessions is suspicious, but since the cron job itself is still scheduled to run again in 3 minutes, I'll just report the empty state without triggering an alert. The main change I need to flag is that the three cron sessions appear to have ended, though this could be a reporting artifact rather than an actual state change.","thinkingSignature":"1ae335127988cbad2839a4c501517c53604d7a969b8aeff4ae5db7a636f64ed5"},{"type":"text","text":"🟡 Orbis-DTLX — 5p Update | 01:57 UTC 15 Apr\n\nChanges detected:\n• Active sessions dropped to **0** — the 3 running cron sessions (5p QLHV monitor, Agent Status to Lead, DTLX 5p Monitor) are no longer showing in sessions_list. Previous heartbeat captured at 01:39 UTC.\n• Telegram group session (-5163901258) delivery issue persists — last confirmed output 01:11 UTC Apr 15.\n\nPipeline: **DEGRADED** (3 cron sessions vanished from active list — possible completion, possible tracking gap)\n• Active sessions: 0\n• MCP: stitch ✅ confluence ✅ gitlab ✅\n\n⚠️ Next cron cycle fires ~02:00 UTC — monitor for session restoration."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":555,"output":791,"cacheRead":13944,"cacheWrite":440,"totalTokens":15730,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stop